类 RangeWorkerPartitioner<I extends org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable,V extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,E extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,M extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable>

    M - Message value
    所有已实现的接口:

    public abstract class RangeWorkerPartitioner<I extends org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable,V extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,E extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable,M extends org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable>
extends Object
implements WorkerGraphPartitioner<I,V,E,M>
    Range partitioning will split the vertices by a key range based on a generic type. This allows vertices that have some locality with the vertex ids to reduce the amount of messages sent. The tradeoffs are that range partitioning is more susceptible to hot spots if the keys are not randomly distributed. Another negative is the user must implement some of the functionality around how to split the key range. Note: This implementation is incomplete, the developer must implement the various methods based on their index type.
